DTEND:20260517T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260513T063930Z
UID:06b74f36-306d-5d1e-bc56-65c0ab22b337
DESCRIPTION:Cycle Toronto will be at Councillor Dianne Saxe's Spring Spect
 acular! This is a free community event held at Christie Pits Park on Victo
 ria Day weekend. There will be a community BBQ\, ice cream\, music\, and l
 ocal vendors.\n\nWe will have an engagement station\, so bring your bike a
 nd one of our fabulous cycling educators will check it out for you!\n\n* D
 ate: Sunday\, May 17th\n* Time: 11 am to 2 pm\n* Location: Christie Pits P
 ark (750 Bloor St W.)\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/saxes_spring_spectacula
 r
LOCATION:Christie Pits Park
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/saxes_spring_spectacular
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bike Match Drop Off at Dufferin Grove Farmers' Market
DTSTART:20260528T190000Z
DTEND:20260528T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260513T063932Z
UID:30e36bb2-5706-5a9a-87c9-cec1efc7dde0
DESCRIPTION:Cycle Toronto is collecting bike donations at the Dufferin Gro
 ve Farmers' Market on Thursday\, May 28 from 3:00 PM - 6:30 PM.\n\nAll don
 ated bikes go toward our Bike Match program\, which was founded by Women's
  Cycling Network and aims to increase access to cycling across the city wh
 ile giving donated bikes a second life.\n\nCycle Toronto and our partner b
 ike hubs collect donated bicycles\, repair them\, and provide them to comm
 unity members in need. Interested participants can sign up through the (ht
 tps://bikematchwcn.com/) Bike Match website.\nURL: https://www.cycleto.ca/
 engagement_station_at_dufferin_grove_farmers_market
LOCATION:
URL:https://www.cycleto.ca/engagement_station_at_dufferin_grove_farmers_ma
 rket
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
